fix: remove Clerk middleware entirely, use @clerk/backend for auth

Root cause: clerkMiddleware() consistently crashed on Vercel's
edge runtime, causing "Internal Server Error" on every /app page.

Solution: bypass the middleware completely.
- Delete proxy.ts (and middleware.ts) entirely
- Auth in API routes: use @clerk/backend authenticateRequest()
  to verify sessions directly from request headers
- Auth in server actions: use getActionAuth() helper that reads
  headers() and verifies via @clerk/backend
- Auth in pages: use client-side useAuth() hook via AuthGuard
- All dashboard pages converted to client components that fetch
  data from API endpoints (/api/dashboard, /api/projects)
- userService refactored to accept clerkId parameter instead
  of calling auth() internally
- Zero imports from @clerk/nextjs/server remain in the codebase
